400 grams McCain Home Chips
80 grams Beef Meatballs
50 grams Harissa Paste
64 grams Mayonnaise
120 grams Coleslaw Mix
2 unit(s) Greek Style Flatbreads
50 grams Greek Style Salad Cheese
50 grams Red Pepper Chilli Jelly

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.
Pop the chips onto one side of a baking tray. Season with salt and pepper. Bake on the top shelf of the oven, 22-24 mins.
When the chips have been baking for 5 mins, add the meatballs to other side of tray.
Bake the meatballs, 18-20 mins. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, in a bowl, mix together the harissa and mayo.
Spoon some harissa mayo onto each serving plate, then set them aside.
Add the coleslaw mix to the remaining harissa mayo and toss. Season with salt and pepper.
Just before the chips and meatballs are ready, pop the flatbreads into the oven, 3-4 mins.

Share the flatbreads between your plates.
Top with the slaw, then the meatballs.
Crumble over the Greek style salad cheese and drizzle over the red pepper chilli jelly.
Serve the chips alongside with the harissa mayo.
Enjoy!